{"search_data": "BiharBihar State Crop Assistance Scheme \u2013 Fasal Sahayata Yojana (Insurance) for FarmersIn this cabinet meeting, the state govt. approved altogether 39 proposals and also sanctions Rs. 215 crore for payment of salaries to teachers and allied staff in 1,128 madrassas.Bihar State Crop Assistance Scheme / Fasal Sahayata YojanaAll the farmers will get this assistance on the basis of threshold yield rate of scheduled crops in an event of crop loss. The assistance amount under this new Crop Insurance Scheme are as follows:-Actual Yield is Reduced by 20% to Threshold Yield Rate \u2013 The state govt. will pay compensation upto a maximum of Rs. 15,000 for 2 hectares (Rs. 7,500 per hectare) to farmers in case the standing crop is damaged by less than 20%.Actual Yield is Reduced by more than 20% to Threshold Yield Rate \u2013 Bihar govt. will pay assistance upto a maximum of Rs. 20,000 for 2 hectares (Rs. 10,000 per hectare) in case of crop failure.This scheme will include all the ryots and non-ryots farmers in the state and this scheme will be launched from Monsoon Scheme for Farmers. State Crop Assistance Scheme will act as a replacement for Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana. Under PMFBY Scheme, the farmers were unable to derive the scheme benefits.In Pradhan Mantri Fasal Bima Yojana, the Centre and state had to bear 49 per cent premium amount each while the farmer had to pay 2% of the premium amount. Till date, state govt. paid Rs 491 crore as premium amount in 2016 while farmers has only received Rs 225 crore by insurance companies.  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now  at  "}